24 
25 template<class PacketClass, void(WorldSession::* HandlerFunction)(PacketClass&)>
26 class PacketHandler : public ClientOpcodeHandler
27 {
28 public:
29  PacketHandler(char const* name, SessionStatus status, PacketProcessing processing) : ClientOpcodeHandler(name, status, processing) { }
30 
31  void Call(WorldSession* session, WorldPacket& packet) const override
32  {
33  PacketClass nicePacket(std::move(packet));
34  nicePacket.Read();
35  (session->*HandlerFunction)(nicePacket);
36  }
37 };
38 
39 template<void(WorldSession::* HandlerFunction)(WorldPacket&)>
40 class PacketHandler<WorldPacket, HandlerFunction> : public ClientOpcodeHandler
41 {
42 public:
43  PacketHandler(char const* name, SessionStatus status, PacketProcessing processing) : ClientOpcodeHandler(name, status, processing) { }
44 
45  void Call(WorldSession* session, WorldPacket& packet) const override
46  {
47  (session->*HandlerFunction)(packet);
48  }
49 };

51 OpcodeTable opcodeTable;
52 
53 template<typename T>
54 struct get_packet_class
55 {
56 };
57 
58 template<typename PacketClass>
59 struct get_packet_class<void(WorldSession::*)(PacketClass&)>
60 {
61  using type = PacketClass;
62 };
63 
64 OpcodeTable::OpcodeTable()
65 {
66  memset(_internalTableClient, 0, sizeof(_internalTableClient));
67 }
68 
69 OpcodeTable::~OpcodeTable()
70 {
71  for (uint16 i = 0; i < NUM_OPCODE_HANDLERS; ++i)
72  delete _internalTableClient[i];
73 }
74 
75 template<typename Handler, Handler HandlerFunction>
76 void OpcodeTable::ValidateAndSetClientOpcode(OpcodeClient opcode, char const* name, SessionStatus status, PacketProcessing processing)
77 {
78  if (uint32(opcode) == NULL_OPCODE)
79  {
80  LOG_ERROR("network", "Opcode %s does not have a value", name);
81  return;
82  }
83 
84  if (uint32(opcode) >= NUM_OPCODE_HANDLERS)
85  {
86  LOG_ERROR("network", "Tried to set handler for an invalid opcode %u", uint32(opcode));
87  return;
88  }
89 
90  if (_internalTableClient[opcode] != nullptr)
91  {
92  LOG_ERROR("network", "Tried to override client handler of %s with %s (opcode %u)", opcodeTable[opcode]->Name, name, uint32(opcode));
93  return;
94  }
95 
96  _internalTableClient[opcode] = new PacketHandler<typename get_packet_class<Handler>::type, HandlerFunction>(name, status, processing);
97 }
98 
99 void OpcodeTable::ValidateAndSetServerOpcode(OpcodeServer opcode, char const* name, SessionStatus status)
100 {
101  if (uint32(opcode) == NULL_OPCODE)
102  {
103  LOG_ERROR("network", "Opcode %s does not have a value", name);
104  return;
105  }
106 
107  if (uint32(opcode) >= NUM_OPCODE_HANDLERS)
108  {
109  LOG_ERROR("network", "Tried to set handler for an invalid opcode %u", uint32(opcode));
110  return;
111  }
112 
113  if (_internalTableClient[opcode] != nullptr)
114  {
115  LOG_ERROR("network", "Tried to override server handler of %s with %s (opcode %u)", opcodeTable[opcode]->Name, name, uint32(opcode));
116  return;
117  }
118 
119  _internalTableClient[opcode] = new PacketHandler<WorldPacket, &WorldSession::Handle_ServerSide>(name, status, PROCESS_INPLACE);
120 }
121 
123 void OpcodeTable::Initialize()
124 {
125 #define DEFINE_HANDLER(opcode, status, processing, handler) \
126  ValidateAndSetClientOpcode<decltype(handler), handler>(opcode, #opcode, status, processing)
127 
128 #define DEFINE_SERVER_OPCODE_HANDLER(opcode, status) \
129  static_assert(status == STATUS_NEVER || status == STATUS_UNHANDLED, "Invalid status for server opcode"); \
130  ValidateAndSetServerOpcode(opcode, #opcode, status)
131

1446 
1447 template<typename T>
1448 inline std::string GetOpcodeNameForLoggingImpl(T id)
1449 {
1450  uint16 opcode = uint16(id);
1451  std::ostringstream ss;
1452  ss << '[';
1453 
1454  if (static_cast<uint16>(id) < NUM_OPCODE_HANDLERS)
1455  {
1456  if (OpcodeHandler const* handler = opcodeTable[id])
1457  ss << handler->Name;
1458  else
1459  ss << "UNKNOWN OPCODE";
1460  }
1461  else
1462  ss << "INVALID OPCODE";
1463 
1464  ss << " 0x" << std::hex << std::setw(4) << std::setfill('0') << std::uppercase << opcode << std::nouppercase << std::dec << " (" << opcode << ")]";
1465  return ss.str();
1466 }
1467 
1468 std::string GetOpcodeNameForLogging(Opcodes opcode)
1469 {
1470  return GetOpcodeNameForLoggingImpl(opcode);
1471 }
